Vice President Kamala Harris addressed a gathering in the Rose Garden to honor the courage and sacrifice of the officers of the United States Capitol Police and the D.C. Metropolitan Police. She recounted her experience of being at the Capitol on January 6th during the violent attack and expressed gratitude towards the officers who risked their lives to protect others. She acknowledged that some officers continue to suffer from injuries, both visible and invisible, and assured them that they are not alone. Harris also mentioned the officers who tragically lost their lives and emphasized the need for vigilance in protecting democracy. She then spoke about the Senate Chamber, where the final vote was tallied to uphold the voice of the American people. She concluded by introducing President Joe Biden as a champion for those who serve in uniform.